Romita Energie Verde , a private
company with Italian and Romanian capital, plans to invest about
41 million euros ($53 million) in a biomass power plant in
 Romania ,  Mediafax  reported today.  Romita seeks to build a 10 megawatt thermal- and power-
plant in a town in the central Romanian county of Cluj, the
Bucharest-based news service said, citing a statement from the
company. Part of the funding for the plant will be secured
through European grants, according to Mediafax.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
